title: For Sale:  FAKE RMR Trijicon - BEWARE - SCAM ALERT
postcontent:
Guys, be aware of Fake Trijicon RMR's on this site.  This guy swears his is real and once I let him know it was fake he denied it and tried to me tell it was a different model, etc...

http://www.armslist.com/posts/3835714/houston-texas-optics-for-sale--trijicon-rmr-sight-adjustable-led

Most of the fakes will be pretty easy to spot, here's what to look for:

No ® (trademark symbol) after the Trijicon logo on the left side
Most are supposed to be RM06 models
All have the same fake serial number---- 080782
Hex adjustment screw, the real RMR's have slotted adjustment screws

Notice the fake one in the link I shared (and flagged) above has all of the fake things to look for on the list.  There is NO WAY it isn't a fake.

If you buy one of these don't expect it to hold zero or last longer than a full magazine.  These were built for airsoft use, not for use with real steal!

In the photos below you can see the real Trijicon RMR on the left and the fake on the right.  Don't let sellers fool you by saying it's a different or newer model.  It's not.  It's a fake!

People trying to scam people out of their hard earned money, especially around the holidays really make me mad.  Flag the ad I listed and please share any other scams you see on this site.  We have to look out for one another!
